events.title: Haemoglobin A1c Level
events.description: The patient's Haemoglobin A1c level was recorded at 45 mmol/mol, indicating potential issues with glucose control and possible diabetes management concerns.

events.title: Body Mass Index (BMI)
events.description: The patient's Body Mass Index was calculated at 18.47 Kg/m², which is considered underweight and may indicate nutritional deficiencies or other health issues.

events.title: Haemoglobin Concentration
events.description: The patient's haemoglobin concentration was measured at 119 g/L, which is slightly below the normal range (115 - 165 g/L), suggesting possible anemia or other hematological concerns.

events.title: Percentage Hypochromic Cells
events.description: The percentage of hypochromic cells was noted at 3.1%, which may indicate iron deficiency or other types of anemia.
